Charlemagne Capital LTD Increased Banco Bradesco Sa (BBD) Position, Cempra Has 0.81 Sentiment


					
						July 24, 2017 - By Pete Kolinski

Charlemagne Capital Ltd increased Banco Bradesco Sa (BBD) stake by 4.54% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Charlemagne Capital Ltd acquired 68,500 shares as Banco Bradesco Sa (BBD)’s stock declined 11.39%. The Charlemagne Capital Ltd holds 1.58M shares with $13.71 million value, up from 1.51M last quarter. Banco Bradesco Sa now has $57.12 billion valuation. The stock rose 0.48% or $0.04 reaching $9.35 per share. About 2.81 million shares traded. Banco Bradesco SA (ADR) (NYSE:BBD) has risen 43.32% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 26.62% the S&P500.







Cempra, Inc. is a clinical-stage pharmaceutical company. The company has market cap of $246.06 million. The Firm focuses on developing differentiated antibiotics for the acute care and community settings to meet medical needs in the treatment of bacterial infectious diseases. It currently has negative earnings. The Company’s product, solithromycin , which is a macrolide and fluoroketolide, is being developed in oral capsules, intravenous (IV) and suspension formulations for the treatment of community-acquired bacterial pneumonia (CABP).
Charlemagne Capital Ltd decreased Vimpelcom Ltd (NASDAQ:VIP) stake by 1.14 million shares to 5.22M valued at $20.01 million in 2016Q4. It also reduced Pampa Energia Sa (NYSE:PAM) stake by 39,700 shares and now owns 114,820 shares. Tal Ed Group (NYSE:XRS) was reduced too. 
Among 6 analysts covering Banco Bradesco SA (NYSE:BBD), 2 have Buy rating, 1 Sell and 3 Hold. Therefore 33% are positive. Banco Bradesco SA had 9 analyst reports since July 29, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The firm has “Sell” rating by Citigroup given on Friday, April 8. The stock of Banco Bradesco SA (ADR) (NYSE:BBD) earned “Sector Perform” rating by Scotia Capital on Wednesday, April 12. The firm earned “Buy” rating on Monday, October 12 by Deutsche Bank. As per Monday, March 14, the company rating was upgraded by Bank of America. The rating was maintained by Goldman Sachs with “Neutral” on Monday, May 2. The rating was initiated by Scotia Capital with “Underperform” on Tuesday, March 15. Deutsche Bank downgraded Banco Bradesco SA (ADR) (NYSE:BBD) on Tuesday, March 22 to “Hold” rating. The firm has “Neutral” rating given on Wednesday, September 21 by Goldman Sachs.
 About 192,291 shares traded. Cempra Inc (CEMP) has declined 75.26% since July 24, 2016 and is downtrending. It has underperformed by 91.96% the S&P500.
Aisling Capital Llc holds 0.78% of its portfolio in Cempra Inc for 1.19 million shares. Hodges Capital Management Inc. owns 1.00 million shares or 0.13% of their US portfolio. Moreover, Two Sigma Securities Llc has 0.07% invested in the company for 71,826 shares. The Connecticut-based P.A.W. Capital Corp has invested 0.06% in the stock. Cam Group Holding A S, a Denmark-based fund reported 891,974 shares.
Since January 1, 0001, it had 0 insider buys, and 1 sale for $533,116 activity. 
Ratings analysis reveals 33% of Cempra’s analysts are positive. Out of 6 Wall Street analysts rating Cempra, 2 give it “Buy”, 2 “Sell” rating, while 2 recommend “Hold”. The lowest target is $2.5 while the high is $32.0. The stock’s average target of $13.88 is 214.03% above today’s ($4.42) share price. CEMP was included in 6 notes of analysts from September 13, 2016. Robert W. Baird downgraded Cempra Inc (NASDAQ:CEMP) on Wednesday, November 2 to “Underperform” rating. The rating was initiated by Raymond James with “Outperform” on Tuesday, September 13. Needham maintained Cempra Inc (NASDAQ:CEMP) rating on Monday, November 7. Needham has “Buy” rating and $15.0 target. On Thursday, December 29 the stock rating was downgraded by WBB Securities to “Hold”. The stock of Cempra Inc (NASDAQ:CEMP) earned “Underweight” rating by Morgan Stanley on Tuesday, November 8. The rating was downgraded by Roth Capital to “Neutral” on Friday, December 30.
Analysts await Cempra Inc (NASDAQ:CEMP) to report earnings on August, 7. They expect $-0.32 EPS, up 37.25% or $0.19 from last year’s $-0.51 per share. After $-0.37 actual EPS reported by Cempra Inc for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts -13.51% EPS growth. 

