Analysts See $-0.56 EPS for Quotient Ltd (QTNT); Charlemagne Capital LTD Cut By $323,575 Its Petrobras Argentina Sa (PZE) Position


					
						July 26, 2017 - By Nellie Frank

 Analysts expect Quotient Ltd (NASDAQ:QTNT) to report $-0.56 EPS on August, 14.They anticipate $0.08 EPS change or 12.50% from last quarter’s $-0.64 EPS. After having $-0.69 EPS previously, Quotient Ltd’s analysts see -18.84% EPS growth. About 73,699 shares traded. Quotient Ltd (NASDAQ:QTNT) has declined 16.87% since July 26, 2016 and is downtrending. It has underperformed by 33.57% the S&P500.







Charlemagne Capital Ltd decreased Petrobras Argentina Sa (PZE) stake by 9.33% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Charlemagne Capital Ltd sold 46,225 shares as Petrobras Argentina Sa (PZE)’s stock rose 29.18%. The Charlemagne Capital Ltd holds 449,363 shares with $3.17M value, down from 495,588 last quarter. Petrobras Argentina Sa now has $2.17B valuation. The stock declined 0.54% or $0.06 reaching $10.98 per share. About 8,578 shares traded. Petrobras Argentina SA ADR (NYSE:PZE) has risen 96.46% since July 26, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 79.76% the S&P500.
Quotient Limited is a diagnostics company. The company has market cap of $209.55 million. The Firm focuses on blood grouping and donor disease screening, which is referred to as transfusion diagnostics. It currently has negative earnings. It is engaged in developing, manufacturing and commercializing conventional reagent products used for blood grouping within the global transfusion diagnostics market.
Investors sentiment decreased to 0.83 in Q4 2016. Its down 1.60, from 2.43 in 2016Q3. It dived, as 7 investors sold Quotient Ltd shares while 5 reduced holdings. 1 funds opened positions while 9 raised stakes. 13.67 million shares or 2.04% more from 13.39 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Royal Bank & Trust Of Canada reported 2,000 shares. Birchview Capital Limited Partnership owns 58,200 shares. Alyeska Limited Partnership invested in 0.03% or 602,422 shares. Clearbridge Ltd Liability Corp holds 0.14% of its portfolio in Quotient Ltd (NASDAQ:QTNT) for 1.25 million shares. Colony Gru Ltd holds 13,360 shares. Blackrock Group Ltd invested in 277,266 shares. California-based Park West Asset Mngmt Lc has invested 0.1% in Quotient Ltd (NASDAQ:QTNT). Blackrock Inv Mngmt Limited Liability Co accumulated 89,250 shares. Perceptive Ltd Liability owns 2.85 million shares or 0.98% of their US portfolio. 123,942 were reported by Blackrock. Geode Mgmt Ltd Com holds 0% or 12,423 shares. Lpl Financial Lc has 0% invested in Quotient Ltd (NASDAQ:QTNT). Blackrock Advsrs Limited Liability reported 691,542 shares stake. Ameriprise reported 0% of its portfolio in Quotient Ltd (NASDAQ:QTNT). Fny Managed Accounts Ltd Liability Corp holds 27,944 shares or 0% of its portfolio.
Among 2 analysts covering Quotient (NASDAQ:QTNT), 2 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 0 Hold. Therefore 100% are positive. Quotient had 3 analyst reports since August 11, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The rating was maintained by UBS on Wednesday, November 4 with “Buy”. Jefferies initiated Quotient Ltd (NASDAQ:QTNT) rating on Tuesday, August 11. Jefferies has “Buy” rating and $30 target. Zacks upgraded it to “Hold” rating and $18 target in Friday, August 14 report.

